Matt ka main message:  
**Pure Reset** bahut aggressive hai.  
**Pure Normalize** kaafi nahi hota modern projects mein.  
**Best Approach**: **Hybrid** → `modern-normalize` + lightweight custom reset.

### 1. Reset vs Normalize vs Hybrid — Quick Comparison

| Approach          | Kya Karta Hai?                                      | Pros                                      | Cons                                              | Best For |
|-------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|----------|
| **Pure Reset**    | Sab margins, padding, fonts, list styles zero kar do | Blank slate, no surprises, full control   | Page bilkul unstyled + inaccessible lagti hai    | Component libraries |
| **Normalize**     | Browser inconsistencies fix karta hai, defaults preserve karta hai | Legible & accessible out-of-the-box       | Phir bhi bahut saare overrides likhne padte hain (margins, headings) | Traditional websites |
| **Hybrid** (Recommended) | Normalize + minimal reset (margins remove + sensible defaults) | Consistency + clean starting point        | Thoda curation chahiye                            | Most modern projects |

**Matt ka Recommendation**: `modern-normalize` import karo + apna lightweight reset add karo.

### 2. Recommended Hybrid CSS (Copy-Paste Ready)

```css
@import "modern-normalize";

/* Global sensible defaults */
:root {
  line-height: 1.5;           /* Accessibility ke liye best */
}

/* Sabse common pain points remove karo */
h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6,
p, figure, ol, ul {
  margin: 0;
}

/* Headings ko inherit karwao (UI apps ke liye best) */
h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
  font-size: inherit;
  font-weight: inherit;
}

/* Lists safely reset (accessibility safe) */
ol[role="list"],
ul[role="list"] {
  list-style: none;
  padding-inline: 0;
}

/* Images responsive banao */
img {
  display: block;
  max-inline-size: 100%;     /* Modern way of max-width: 100% */
}
```

**Extra Global Rule** (har project mein daal do):
```css
*,
*::before,
*::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}
```

### 3. Important Insights from the Article

- **Line-height: 1.5** → Default se better readability + WCAG friendly.
- **Headings inherit font** → Modern apps mein `<h1>` har jagah same size nahi hota, isliye inherit better.
- **List reset with `[role="list"]`** → Screen readers ke liye safe (VoiceOver issue avoid hota hai).
- **Images** → `display: block` + `max-inline-size: 100%` se overflow nahi hota.
- **When to use `revert`** → Long-form content (blog, articles) mein default styles wapas laane ke liye:
  ```css
  .article :where(h1, h2, h3, h4, h5) {
    all: revert;
  }
  ```
- Reset ko project ke **shuruaat** mein hi decide karo. Beech mein add karna mushkil hota hai.

### 4. Quick Decision Guide

- **Tailwind CSS** use kar rahe ho? → Preflight already hybrid hai (best).
- **Vanilla CSS / Custom project**? → `modern-normalize` + upar wala lightweight reset.
- **Heavy design system / components**? → Pure reset ya Tailwind Preflight style.
- **Traditional content-heavy site**? → Normalize + minimal margin reset.